 Career History



Executive Vice President, Product & Innovation

                                    2012 - Current                


Snipp Interactive Inc.


                  Snipp Interactive, Inc. engages in the development and sale of mobile marketing solutions. The firm provides mobile promotions and contests; purchase promotions and receipt processing; loyalty programs; rebate solutions; data analytics; and augmented reality and applications. It operates through the following geographical segments: United States, International, and Canada. The company was founded by Ritesh Bhavnani and Atul Sabharwal in March 2007 and is headquartered in Bethesda, MD.                




Director-Print Mobile Solutions

                                    Prior                


Condé Nast Entertainment, Inc.


                  Condé Nast Entertainment, Inc. develops film, television, and premium digital video programming. The firm's portfolio include Vogue, Vanity Fair, Glamour, Brides, Self, GQ, GQ Style, The New Yorker, Condé Nast Traveler, Allure, Architectural Digest, Bon Appétit, Epicurious, Wired, W, Golf Digest, Golf World, Teen Vogue, Ars Technica, The Scene, Pitchfork and Backchannel. The company was founded by Conde Montrose Nast and Pat Connolly in 2011 and is headquartered in New York, NY.                





